ed the Civil Service.  I got to know him in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cambridge{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
.  Other friends have dispersed from Cambridge days, such as Dick Gilling, who was with me on the Film Society Committee, and moved to Australia, but I\rquote ve seen him on a few occasions, going to Australia.  Mike and Mary Teitz from 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Berkeley{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} are very good friends, saw them a few weeks ago when they were here.  In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cambridge{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Gee and Karen Benveniste still remain very good friends, although we don\rquote t see them so often.  We had a sort of funny European air enclave in Berkeley \endash 
