g trams off city streets on to railway tracks into the countryside, and we want to try to do that in other places, especially Blackpool, which is, of course, the place I grew up in, and I wanted it as my present to Blackpool.  By the way, we haven\rquote 
t spoken about the fact that I was chair of the Urban Regeneration company up there for four years. We didn\rquote t do much, except fail to get the casino, when Gordon Brown blocked it, which were four very frustrating years, and when I left, I said, 
\'93I\rquote m going to do something.  I\rquote ll get the tram train here\'94, and I\rquote ve been battling to do that for the past three years, with precious little success.  I\rquote m not sure if I\rquote m going to succeed, but at least we\rquote 
re still working on it, yeah.
